Description: backport modern nv_ioremap_nocache behavior from 440.64
 Modern x86 kernels removed ioremap_nocache(); plain ioremap() supplies the
 intended non-cacheable device mapping semantics.  Keep the allocation record
 label for the nocache wrapper unchanged.
Origin: backport, NVIDIA 440.64 ioremap compatibility pattern
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-07-20

--- a/common/inc/nv-linux.h	2026-07-20 07:24:40.344359269 +0000
+++ b/common/inc/nv-linux.h	2026-07-20 07:24:40.432359076 +0000
@@ -690,7 +690,11 @@
 
 static inline void *nv_ioremap_nocache(NvU64 phys, NvU64 size)
 {
+#if defined(NV_IOREMAP_NOCACHE_PRESENT)
     void *ptr = ioremap_nocache(phys, size);
+#else
+    void *ptr = ioremap(phys, size);
+#endif
     VM_ALLOC_RECORD(ptr, size, "vm_ioremap_nocache");
     return ptr;
 }
